  "id": "019cdcdc-fd01-7d11-b0d7-9adc438596e1",
  "content": "### Fix 2: Markdown AST Cross-References (D73)\n\n### Fix 3: Declaration + Usage Tracking (D74)\n\n**Crate:** `corvia-kernel` (in `chunking_pipeline.rs`)\n\n**Approach:** Two-pass post-processing after all chunks are processed. First pass collects symbol definitions, second pass finds cross-file usages.\n\n**New function:**\n```\ndiscover_cross_file_relations(chunks: &[ProcessedChunk]) -> Vec<ChunkRelation>\n```\n\n**Pass 1 — Collect definitions:**\n- Scan each chunk's `metadata.chunk_type` for definition types (`\"struct\"`, `\"trait\"`, `\"enum\"`, `\"function\"`)\n- Extract the declared name from chunk content (first line: `pub struct Foo`, `pub trait Bar`, `fn baz()`)\n- Build definition index: `HashMap<String, Vec<(source_file, start_line)>>`\n- Only track CamelCase names (types/traits) and SCREAMING_CASE (constants)\n- Minimum name length: 3 chars\n- Skip Rust standard library types: `String`, `Vec`, `HashMap`, `Option`, `Result`, `Box`, `Arc`, `Mutex`, `Rc`, `Cell`, `RefCell`, `Pin`, `Future`, `Stream`, `Iterator`, `Display`, `Debug`, `Clone`, `Copy`, `Send`, `Sync`, `Default`, `From`, `Into`, `TryFrom`, `TryInto`, `AsRef`, `AsMut`, `Deref`, `Drop`, `Fn`, `FnMut`, `FnOnce`, `Error`, `Ord`, `PartialOrd`, `Eq`, `PartialEq`, `Hash`, `Sized`\n\n**Pass 2 — Find usages:**\n- For each chunk, scan content for references to defined symbols\n- Skip self-references (chunk defines the symbol)\n- Skip same-file references (already covered by `contains`/`implements`)\n- For each cross-file usage, create:",
